The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, November 04, 2002  Calcutta Column
				 																																									The land below the approach to Vidyasagar Setu has been turned into a pigsty, where around 150 to 200 pigs have been accommodated. The possibility of an encephalitis outbreak cannot be ruled out. Besides, a large portion of the plot has been occupied by makeshift structures. The entire stretch, as a result, looks very dirty. 				 																																									D.G. Pillai,				 																																									Hastings.				 																																									It has become a routine affair for most Kali puja committees to arrange concerts near the pandals. A huge amount of subscription is raised for the soiree and local residents are persuaded to pitch in. Its time we protested such activities.				 																																									Rabindranath Kar,				 																																									Sankar Ghosh Lane.
